node.text:
In this episode of my 'How To' series, I show you exactly how to set up AND dismantle the squat rack! 🏋️‍♀️

Now if you think this piece of equipment is VERY intimating... you're definitely not alone! I'm sure there's a lot of women that avoid using the squat rack when they are in the gym... and that is exactly why I have started this video series. 

BUT I want you to take me with you to the gym next time, and give yourself the time to get comfortable using the Squat Rack. And if you still feel uncomfortable, bring a friend to the gym with you so you can both learn how to use this machine together.... I promise it's not as intimidating as it looks! 🙂

This machine is used in my new High Intensity Strength Program, so if you love this machine OR if you've never used it before and want to start - I recommend my new and improved gym program for you! You can try it today by downloading @Sweat via the link in my bio! 

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntesnityStrengthWithKayla

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Workout #GymWorkout

node.text:
In episode 3 of of my 'How To' series, I'm showing you exactly how to set up and use a resistance band! 😄

There are so many types of resistance bands that can be used for many different exercises, but I want to show you how you can attach longer resistance bands to a bar to help you with things like assisted pull-ups and chin-ups!

You will usually find resistance bands hanging up around the gym, or you can bring your own to ensure you've got the right size available for you. ✔️

The key thing to remember with resistance bands is that the THICKER bands have MORE resistance than the thinner bands. In the case of a pull-up or chin up, the thicker band will assist you more (as there is more resistance) making it easier for you to pull yourself up to complete the exercise.

However, in most other cases (like resistance band tricep extensions or bicep curls) the thinner resistance bands actually make the exercise easier than the thicker ones! And if this confuses you a little bit, don't worry! You will instantly feel the difference and know which one is right to use when you try them out. 😅

I hope this video gives you the confidence to try an assisted pull-up or chin-up next time you are in the gym! I have included these in my new High Intensity Strength Program, which you can try by downloading @Sweat today! 

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatApp #SweatCommunity #gym #gymworkout

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text:
Episode ✌️ of my 'How To' series is all about how to use the Cable & Pulley machine! 
This machine can look quite intimidating at first because there are so many parts to it. I've heard my clients say that they used to walk up to the machine and use whatever attachment is already there because they are too scared (or don't know how) to change them... which I totally understand.

Hopefully, this video will help you gain the confidence to firstly... use this machine, and secondly... use the machine exactly the way you want to! So next time you're in the gym, take me with you and give yourself the time to learn how these parts actually work. I promise it's easier than you have imagined! 😊

My High Intensity Strength program includes the use of this machine, and the @Sweat app will tell you exactly which attachment you need to complete the exercise which should help you build confidence, too! You can try my new gym program today via the link in my bio 😊

PS. All the videos that I will be sharing over the next week have been filmed before Adelaide's current lockdown. Stay safe ❤️

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #Workout #Gym #gymworkout 

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text:
INTRODUCING MY NEW 'HOW TO' SERIES - GYM EDITION 🌟
As gyms begin to re-open around the world, I want everyone to feel confident and comfortable getting back to their gym-based workouts.

I also know a lot of women feel intimidated about going to the gym, especially when it comes to using large equipment... so it's for these reasons I want to show you exactly HOW TO navigate a gym setting. In this series, I'll be taking you the step-by-step process as to how to set up and use different equipment around the gym.

To kick the series off, we're starting with the equipment that was requested most by YOU, #SWKCommunity...  THE LEG PRESS! 

We have a variety of gym-based programs in the @Sweat app that involves using the Leg Press, including my new and improved High-Intensity Strength program. So, next time you're in the gym... I want you to take me with you and allow yourself the time to get comfortable with using these bigger machines. Before you know it, you'll wish you stopped avoiding them sooner! 

I hope by the end of this episode you feel a lot LESS intimidated and a lot MORE empowered to use this machine in your training. 

If you're keen to start using the Leg Press in your workouts, I recommend trying my new and improved High Intensity Strength program. It uses larger machines, free weights and bodyweight exercises to help women get fitter and get stronger! You can try it today for free using @Sweat's 7-Day free trial (link in bio)!

It has been great to bring you even more new gym programs to Sweat and from now on we will be working with @iFIT to help deliver even more choice and variety to you all!

#SWK #SweatwithKayla #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #LegPress #gym #gymequipment #gymtutorial

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text: Let’s do this!! Take me anywhere with you and let’s train abs together !! (No equipment) EXPRESS WORKOUT

"But Kayla, I don't have time to workout today!!" 
... are you sure about that?! 🤣🤣

If this sounds like you, I'm here to tell you that there is almost ALWAYS time to squeeze in a workout! You just have to start telling yourself that any amount of time working out it's worth it! 
 
I've created this 5-minute "follow-along" lower body workout that should have you breaking a sweat and feeling accomplished in a short amount of time! I'm ready to work out with you right now, but it's up to YOU to set aside the time to get your body moving today! 

✅ Squat Pulse - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

✅ Curtsey Lunge - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

✅ Glute Bridge Walkout - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

 Do 3 laps

✅ Squat Pulse finisher - 30 secs

I certainly felt the burn after that!! Did you? 🔥😅

If you love the thought of an express workout - there are SO many incredible programs in the @Sweat app that are ready and waiting for you! Head to the link in my bio for a 7-Day free trial and get moving today!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatwithKayla 

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatwithKayla #SweatCommunity #ExpressWorkout #Workout

Are your glute bridges actually working your glutes? Or just hurting your lower back? 🤔
Glute bridges are one of those exercises that look quite easy to do... but they can hurt the wrong muscles if done incorrectly! 

I've noticed that some people push their hips as high as they can, causing them to over-extend and put pressure on their lower back. If this sounds like you, or you haven't been feeling the burn in your glutes when doing glute bridges, I want you to watch this video and practice my number one tip! 

You should absolutely be feeling your glutes burn if you do this! 🔥
Let me know if this has helped you!

node.text:
This is an easy one to get wrong ❌ 
So if you do Ab Bikes often, I want you to take the time to learn how to get them right! ✅

In this video, I break down the exercise into smaller steps to help you perfect your form. Once you've mastered each movement, add each step in until you build up to a full Ab Bike! 

Here are some do's and don'ts to remember:
DO
✅Rest hands in front of ears
✅Rotate at the torso
✅Bring knees in close to the chest
✅Extend your legs in a push and pull motion
✅Elevate your shoulders

DON'T
❌Pull your neck up with your hands behind your head
❌Do small in and out motions with your legs
❌Curve your back away from the floor

What other exercises do you want to learn from me? Comment below!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatwithKayla

#SWK #SWKcommunity #Exercises #BBG #SweatwithKayla

node.text:
Right, so today I'm going to break down the burpee for you to make it easier.

It's still not going to be EASY (it's a burpee haha!!)... but these tips will make it easier to do 😅⁣ You're still going to #SweatwithKayla and you'll find burpees in my High Intensity program. There's a link in my bio for a 7 day FREE trial of the @Sweat app. 

Follow this and see how it feels:
✅Start at the top of your mat
✅Put your hands down in front of your feet as you squat down
✅Jump back into a push up position
✅Make sure your wrist and shoulder is in line
✅Back nice and straight
✅Make sure you're stable and have a strong core 
✅Jump back in with feet apart (not together!)
✅Stand up and do your jump
✅Find your rhythm

Some common mistakes:
❌Starting with your hands too far in front of you 
❌Not holding your core tight throughout each movement
❌Letting your back dip down into an unstable position
❌Jumping in too far with your feet and putting pressure on your knees
❌Arching your back too much before jumping to a standing position

Now, I've shown you the correct technique how do your burpees feel?

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

#SweatwithKayla #SWKcommunity #Sweat #Sweatcommunity #fitness #burpee

node.text:
For a lot of women around the world, the last 12 months have been tough. For many of you it meant an adjustment to working out at home, or perhaps, it meant losing the time, space or motivation to work out all together. I want you to know that you’re not alone in facing these challenges. We see you and and at @Sweat we want to help.

I want to introduce you to Sweat’s new MOVE AGAIN programs, designed specifically for those who have had a break in their fitness journey due to the pandemic.

These four new beginner level programs consist of two 20-minute workouts a week for four weeks and are led by four inspiring trainers that are dedicated to help you form healthy habits and get you back into fitness. 

👉 Bodyweight Strength with Anissia (@avh__fitness)
🌟 When Anissia isn’t playing basketball, she’s all about strength and bodyweight circuits. Her approach to fitness is all about getting back to basics and her Bodyweight Strength workouts require absolutely no equipment.

👉 Low Impact HIIT with Samantha (@so_manti)
🌟 With Samantha you can expect a fast-paced and upbeat style to her Low Impact HIIT workouts which are perfect for getting a quick sweat up in a short amount of time.

👉 Strength & Cardio with Marilyn (@fitwithmarilyn)
🌟 Marilyn’s approach to fitness is about maximising your time with fun and dynamic workouts to help you build form and to find your love for moving again. You’ll feel strong off the back of these workouts and the combination of rep based strength and timed based cardio.

👉 Low Impact Strength with Kelsey (@kelseywells)
🌟 Now Kelsey is one of my best friends and she has been part of the Sweat family for a while now and we so are excited to be adding a low-impact strength program. Kelsey’s new dumbbell based workouts are great to build your confidence using weights and will have you feeling strong again in no time.

We’ve designed each program to support your physical and mental health. We want you to remember how good it feels to move again!

So why not take advantage of our Sweat 7-day free trial and start moving again

www.kaylaitsines.com/moveagain

#MoveAgain #Sweat #Sweatcommunity #SWKcommunity #KaylaItsines

node.title: Introducing Move Again - 4 New Beginner Level Programs

I absolutely LOVE doing ab workouts, and clearly many of you ladies in the #SweatCommunity feel the same way because they are my most requested workouts! ⁣😍
⁣
This Advanced Ab Follow Along uses ZERO equipment and will put most people through their paces. 5 minutes of 5 exercises with a rest in-between each, let's do this! 

✅ Single-Arm and Leg Jackknife - 45 sec
✅ Rest - 15 sec
✅ Straight-Leg Raise & Hip Lift - 45 sec
✅ Rest - 15 sec
✅ Bent Leg Toe Taps - 45 sec 
✅ Rest - 15 sec
✅ X Plank - 45 sec 
✅ Rest - 15 sec
✅ Plank - 45 sec 
✅ Rest - 15 sec

Complete 1 lap!

This is perfect to add on to the end of your workouts, so I want you to SAVE this video next time you train! For even more ab workouts like this try my Zero Equipment program @Sweat today! 

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

#SweatwithKayla #SWKcommunity #AbsWorkout #ZeroEquipment #Sweat

node.text:
I AM #SWEATMADE. ARE YOU?
For me, being fit is only part of my story.

Training isn’t just about building a strong body. It’s about giving your self-worth a workout.

It’s about pushing past the excuses, the doubt and the desire to quit.

Through sweat, through the power of action, we can achieve almost anything.

Whatever it is that you want, I want to help you get there.

I want you to feel as good on the inside, as you do on the outside.

Because the best version of you, she’s waiting to sweat.

I am #SweatMade. Are you?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by KAYLA ITSINES on August 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'It doesn't get easier, you just get stronger.'.

node.text:
When you first start working out, you might find an exercise, like push ups really difficult to do. You might only be able to manage a few reps on your knees, and that’s okay! 

As you go on, you might start to notice some changes . . . before, you could only manage 10 push ups on your knees. Now, you can do 15, and you don’t even have to think about it! It’s easy! 

So in your next workout, you think ‘right, I’m going to try some push ups on my toes’. You might only be able to do a few, and then drop back down to your knees, but WOW, you’ve never been able to do any on your toes before!! That is such an achievement, and now you know you can do it 🙌

And down the track, you feel strong enough to ONLY do push ups on your toes! From only being able to do a couple of reps on your knees at the start, to now doing full reps, it's amazing to see how far you have come. The push ups didn't get easier - you just got stronger. 

It's the same with difficulties that you might face in life. You might face challenge, and they don't get easier, you just develop the strength, courage, and perseverance to overcome them ❤️

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Motivation #Quote 

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

node.text:
I AM DETERMINED.
Determination, to me, is when confidence, resilience and strength combine to create this powerful sense of being. It gives me purpose and a reason to give 100% towards everything I do. 

When I really sit back and think about it, my determination stems from my childhood upbringing...

Growing up, my sister and I were taught that nothing in life comes easy and that anything that is truly worth it takes hard work. My grandparents always taught me that and to be honest, they have worked so hard for their entire life and they are my biggest inspiration. I often think if they can do it, I can too. "If there's a will, there's a way".

As a kid, my family gave me the confidence to be curious, to try new things and to question the way things were done. This mindset allowed me to follow my own path, which eventually, gave me a strong vision for what I wanted my future to look like. I am forever grateful and feel so privileged for the opportunity they gave me to make this future of my own. 

I truly believe that determination is about knowing what you want and having the DESIRE to make it happen. You may not know exactly how you're going to get there, or how long it will take... but you've got a firm idea of what you're working towards and you're not going to let anything get in the way. 

I rely on my determination every single day... In my training, in business, and especially as a mum. I'm not afraid to look forward, set a vision and work hard to make things happen.

I am determined. Are you?

node.text:
THE REAL REASON I DECIDED TO START WORKING OUT FOR JUST 28 MINUTES... 
Read this caption👇👇👇

So many of you already know how passionate I am about my 28-minute workouts, so much so that I built the entire @Sweat app off the back of the 28-minute concept. Why? Because it gets results. You can always find time to fit it in. And it never gets boring...

But what so many of you don't know is how I came about this 28-minute 'revelation'....

It all started when I was 17 when I joined a local gym, which, without my knowledge, was largely a bodybuilders gym.... 

I felt SO out of place, SO lost and SO intimidated by everything and everyone at that gym. Literally, the only way ​I could talk myself into actually going and sticking to a workout plan was by convincing myself to build up the confidence to go for JUST 30 minutes. 

... And you bet that 30 minutes included a few minutes to walk in and out of there as fast as I could!!! 🤣

I was honestly that intimidated.

BUT - eventually, I started to realise that my quick workouts were actually working... really well! In my head, I knew I only had a short amount of time to smash out my sets, so naturally, I made sure I was working at a higher intensity to get the most out of it in the shortest amount of time. And yeah, it really worked! I was so happy with the results that remember trying to convince all my friends that 28 mins is all you need. They know that.... now 🤣

..... a few years on I got my PT licence, started my e-books and well, the rest is history! 

Isn't it funny how stepping outside of your comfort zone can take you on these crazy paths? 😊

www.Kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatApp

node.text:
I AM STRONG. 
The real power of strength is not is what's on the outside, but it's what's within all of us. 

It's not about how heavy we can lift, or how high we can jump - it's about our ability to dig deep and find the mental strength to keep going when we really feel like giving up. 

For me, strength is the ability to get out of bed when I feel like sleeping in. It's the choice I make to do the workout that I'd much rather put off. It's facing my fears head-on and not succumbing to challenges, but working hard to defeat them. It's about setting goals that will push me. Becoming comfortable with failure. And not being afraid to show up again and again and again in pursuit of a better version of me. 

I have always found strength in determination, and more recently, I have discovered strength in love, too. 

Since becoming a mum to Arna, I've had to be stronger than I've ever needed to be before. As mums - we are carers, role models, and our child's biggest support. No matter what we are going through, and no matter how bad we sometimes feel like giving up - we are always there for them. For me, motherhood unlocked a level of strength I didn't even know I had in me. And that level of strength, ladies, should never be taken for granted. ❤️

I am strong. Are you?

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #motivation #mum

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Dogs #dogsofinstagram

I AM RESILIENT.
Never underestimate how resilient we are as human beings. Sometimes you don't even know you have it in you until you truly need to rely on it. 

Over the past few years, my body has been through more than it has in its lifetime. From my first endo-surgery, to having Arna, and all the setbacks in between - at times it has felt like I'm taking one step forward and two steps back... and the battle is still going. It's been an exhausting journey so far - and to be honest, it hasn’t always been an easy journey and there have been many times where I've found it difficult to continue moving forward. 

But I didn't. I chose to get back up again, and again, and again - and show up for myself every single day. My resilience was there to hold me up when my body physically struggled, and I am so grateful that didn't let these setbacks define me. 

To be honest, I didn't truly know what resilience was until I went through all these complications recently. I used to think that showing up every single day for my clients was good enough - but I was wrong. Showing up for myself is actually what resilience is all about. And I will keep getting back up for me. 

I am resilient. Are you?

 #SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #resilient #health

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by KAYLA ITSINES on August 11, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Your habits decide your future.'.

node.text:
Absolutely right. ✔️
You are only as good as your actions, and these actions shape who you are and who you will become. 

Sometimes, as humans, we have a picture in our head of who we think we are. But then when it comes to our day-to-day reality - this perception doesn't align with our actions.

So for example, you may consider yourself a really productive person that aims to get the most out of life. But in reality, you spend a lot of the day watching TV or sleeping in or scrolling on social media.

Or, you might consider yourself as a really health-conscious person, but your eating or exercise habits might actually say otherwise. 

What I'm trying to get at here, is that if you want to be something, you have to take action!
... If you want to be a productive person, you need to start making productive habits.
... If you want to be a healthy person, you need to start taking steps towards a healthy life. 

It's actually quite a simple concept.. but it can so easily get lost in the business of life. 

So #SWKCommunity - what actions are you going to take to make sure you are who you want to be in your future? 🤔

#SWK #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #motivation #quote #quoteoftheday

node.text:
I AM CONFIDENT.
Confidence is something that no one is born with, and is completely unique to every single one of us.  It takes so much time and mental strength to build, yet if you let it slip, it can be stolen away in a second. 

To me, confidence stems from knowing what is important to YOU, and being firm on what you want to stand for in this world. 🌏 This may take years of self-exploration, a million mistakes and countless uncomfortable experiences to build. And that's exactly why it is so powerful.

Being confident is standing up for yourself when you know it's right. It's about taking your own path, and not being distracted by the noise. It's uncomfortable and uplifting at the same time - and if nothing else, your confidence will be there to back you when others won't.

I'll admit - the path to confidence isn't easy. But when you've got it, it really does shine brighter than anything else in a room. 💛

I am confident. Are you?

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #Confidence #Fitness #Health

node.text:
Micha, I have loved following your fitness journey and seeing your progress!! ✨ I think it’s so important that you focus on your mental and emotional progress, and not just on the physical. It takes lots of hard work to become the most confident and strongest version of you, and I’m so proud of you!! 💪

Some words from Micha (@mum_sweatlife): 
“Progress looks linear but it’s not.
It looks like a start and a finish but it’s not.
It looks like a before and after but it’s not.

You can’t fit years of progress into one tiny Instagram square.

You can’t fit the mental strength that gets built day in and day out when you never give up on yourself or the confidence you build as you get stronger. 💪🏻💦

You can’t fit the interrupted workouts, the doubt, the loong weeks where you didn’t see any “progress” but you bloody keep going anyway.

You can’t fit the sweat and the tears. The sore muscles. The proud moments. The reps. The thousands and thousands of reps. 🏋🏻‍♀️

You can’t fit the strength it takes to keep going no matter what.
No matter what people tell you. No matter what people think of you and your journey.
No matter how long it takes.

You just can’t fit progress like that in a box. You just have get out there and feel it for yourself! 💪🏻💦”
